THE AIRCRAFT CRASHED IN AN OPEN FLIGHT SHORTLY AFTER TAKEOFF AND WAS 
DESTROYED BY FIRE. THERE WERE NO WITNESSES TO THE ACCIDENT. THE PILOT 
REPORTEDLY STATED HE NEEDED TO DEPART MANHATTAN BY 0500 MST TO ARRIVE 
IN HELENA BEFORE 0600 MST WHEN THE AIR TRAFFIC CONTROL TWR OPENED AS HIS AIRCRAFT WAS NOT 
RADIO EQUIPPED. THE WRECKAGE WAS DISCOVERED AT 1430 MST BY ANOTHER 
AIRCRAFT. THE PRIVATE AIRSTRIP AT MANHATTAN WAS NOT EQUIPPED WITH ANY RUNWAY 
LIGHTING. INSPECTION OF THE AIRCRAFT AND ENG DID NOT DISCLOSE ANY 
MECHANICAL FAILURE/MALFUNCTION. 
